          {
            "question": "Which AI video model is the best?",
            "answer": "It depends on your needs. Veo 3.1 Quality produces the most photorealistic results up to 4K. Seedance 2.0 excels at cinematic video with audio and lip sync. Wan 2.7 offers versatile T2V and I2V modes. HappyHorse 1.0 is the best open-source option, ranked #1 on Artificial Analysis."
          },
          {
            "question": "Which AI video model is the cheapest?",
            "answer": "Veo 3.1 Lite at just 8 credits per generation is the cheapest option. Hailuo 02 T2V Standard costs 24 credits for a 6-second 768p video. Seedance 2.0 Fast 480p costs 12 credits/second. HappyHorse 1.0 is open-source and free to use."
          },
          {
            "question": "Which AI video model has the highest resolution?",
            "answer": "Veo 3.1 (all tiers) supports up to 4K output. Wan 2.7, Hailuo 2.3 Pro, and Hailuo 02 Pro support up to 1080p. Seedance 2.0 supports up to 720p."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can I try these AI video models for free?",
            "answer": "Yes! All models on our platform offer free sign-up credits. You can test every model before committing to a paid plan."
          },
          {
            "question": "What's the difference between Veo 3.1 Lite, Fast, and Quality?",
            "answer": "Veo 3.1 Lite is the cheapest at 8 credits per 720p generation — great for quick tests. Veo 3.1 Fast at 16 credits offers faster processing with good quality. Veo 3.1 Quality at 120 credits provides the highest visual fidelity and photorealism. All support up to 4K resolution."
          },
          {
            "question": "What's the difference between Hailuo 2.3 and Hailuo 02?",
            "answer": "Hailuo 2.3 is image-to-video only (requires an image input). Hailuo 02 supports both text-to-video and image-to-video with more resolution options including 512p, 768p, and 1080p."
          }
        ]
